content.description: Sketchy traverse by the creek. After some cleaning, it'll be way better. Lots of ledges and some big pockets. Bring multiple pads.
content.protection: At least one crash pad, preferably more.
content.location: Start above the slopey, bad side pull on the left. It moves up and to the right all the way to where the dirt trail meets the cliff.

content.description:
I've heard rumors of the Posey Crag in this general area. Not much is found online. The only website with a bit of documentation says it is not worth the drive.  

  YMMV 

  If you are in the area, please document it! I'm hoping that listing this area will make Indiana a little less barren.
